[The state of South Carolina can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2752704,13112. Colleton County can be seen on the map at http://geology.com/county-map/south-carolina-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ

Eastern equine encephalitis can be prevented in horses by a vaccine, which is often combined with West Nile virus vaccine. Therefore, one injection and the animal is protected from at least 2 diseases. The vaccine needs to be given twice, 3 weeks apart, and in areas where EEE is most prevalent it is recommended to revaccinate every 4-6 months as the immunity to EEE wanes rather rapidly.

There are also mosquito sprays for horses that should be used.

People should be cautious to use mosquito repellant with DEET, wear long sleeves, and remember that dusk and dawn have the highest number of mosquitoes and should be avoided. - Mod.TG]
